   <narrative xml:lang="EN">BRAVE-Utlisation des eaux souteraines pour la r&#xE9;silience communautaire</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1.WP1 Organize a 1day in-house w/shop to train 6 field facilitators on the data collection instruments and vulnerability indices
2.Farmer Listening Workshop &amp; End of season evaluation surveys/interviews in each of 4 BF communities via Farmers Listening Groups to evaluate livelihood impact indicators 
3.1-day Feedback Workshop for 30 at beginning Y3 for stakeholders at local Govt level to feedback on impact of GW planning tools,to facilitate ownership &amp; management of new tools &amp; M&amp;
4.Organize District Stakeholder meeting for 30 people - community reps &amp; local Govt officials from community districts&amp; Heads decentralized depts &amp; NGOs to introduce BRAVE2,general methods&amp;vulnerability
5.1d Training w/shop reviewing use of GW planning tool at beginning of season in Y2 (March/April) and livelihood impact indicators from WP1 for CBO coordinators, PDRABS + 6 field assist</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Rural communities will have better planning for their activity in connection with groundwater and improve its use</narrative>
  </description>
